OL,4,G````````````B PRIMARY G``````Su;/!G````
OL,5,BCHRISTMASGby Michael, seven, St        
OL,6,GPatrick's Primary School, Coatbridge   
OL,7,COne day a carpenter called Joseph and a
OL,8,Clady called Mary were told from an     
OL,9,CAngel they were going to have a baby.  
OL,10,CBut there was a problem because the    
OL,11,Clandowner Caesar was going to have a   
OL,12,Ccensus and the book they would have to 
OL,13,Csign was in Bethlehem.                 
OL,14,C                                       
OL,15,CThey went to a place in Bethlehem. It  
OL,16,Cwas an inn. They knocked on the door   
OL,17,Cbut no answer. Same with the next. Then
OL,18,Cthey found a stable to sleep in. And   
OL,19,Cthen the baby was born.                
OL,20,G``````````````````````````````````2/4``
